            "body": "Why is this hyper-focused on selecting *windows*? Buffers, tabs, etc, have the same situation.\n\nWhat is missing from `vim.ui.select` , which already exists?\n\nPerhaps what is needed is that `vim.ui.select()` accepts a standard form like `{ name: string, id: number, ... }` and presents it in a standard way. Perhaps keyed by `kind`, so then\n\n    vim.ui.select({ kind = 'window' }, wins)\n\nknows to present windows.\n\nAnyway, this issue does not present an interface that actually makes sense in core, so I'm closing it.\n",
